v\\\" \\\"staging\\\" \\\"prod\\\"\\n#USAGE }\\n#USAGE flag \\\"--dry-run\\\" help=\\\"Preview changes without deploying\\\"\\n#USAGE flag \\\"--region <region>\\\" help=\\\"AWS region\\\" default=\\\"us-east-1\\\" env=\\\"AWS_REGION\\\"\\n\\nENVIRONMENT=\\\"${usage_environment?}\\\"\\nREGION=\\\"${usage_region?}\\\"\\nDRY_RUN=\\\"${usage_dry_run:-false}\\\"\\n\\nif [[ \\\"$DRY_RUN\\\" == \\\"true\\\" ]]; then\\n  echo \\\"DRY RUN: Would deploy to $ENVIRONMENT in $REGION\\\"\\nelse\\n  echo \\\"Deploying to $ENVIRONMENT in $REGION...\\\"\\n  ./scripts/deploy.sh \\\"$ENVIRONMENT\\\" \\\"$REGION\\\"\\nfi\\n\\n```\\n\\n--------------------------------\\n\\n### File Task with Usage Arguments (Bash)\\n\\nSource: https://github.com/jdx/mise/blob/main/docs/tasks/task-configuration.md\\n\\nThis bash script demonstrates how to define task arguments and flags directly within comments using the `#USAGE` directive. It supports `env` attributes for environment variable fallback and specifies input and output files.\\n\\n```bash\\n#!/usr/bin/env bash\\n#USAGE arg \\\"<input>\\\" env=\\\"INPUT_FILE\\\" help=\\\"Input file to process\\\"\\n#USAGE flag \\\"-o --output <file>\\\" env=\\\"OUTPUT_FILE\\\" help=\\\"Output file\\\" default=\\\"out.txt\\\"\\n\\necho \\\"Processing ${usage_input?} -> ${usage_output?}\\\"\\n```\\n\\n--------------------------------\\n\\n### Configure Task Arguments with Usage Field in TOML\\n\\nSource: https://github.com/jdx/mise/blob/main/docs/tasks/toml-tasks.md\\n\\nDefines task arguments using the 'usage' field in a TOML file. Arguments are exposed as environment variables prefixed with 'usage_'. This is the recommended approach for defining arguments.\\n\\n```toml\\n[tasks.test]\\nusage = '''\\narg \\\"<file>\\\" help=\\\"Test file to run\\\" default=\\\"all\\\"\\nflag \\\"--format <format>\\\" help=\\\"Output format\\\" default=\\\"text\\\"\\nflag \\\"-v --verbose\\\" help=\\\"Enable verbose output\\\"\\n'''\\nrun = 'cargo test ${usage_file?} --format ${usage_format?}'\\n```\\n\\n--------------------------------\\n\\n### Define Task with Usage Arguments (TOML)\\n\\nSource: https://github.com/jdx/mise/blob/main/docs/tasks/task-configuration.md\\n\\nThis TOML snippet shows how to define a task with a custom `usage` field. The `usage` field specifies an argument `<file>` with a help message and a default value. The `run` field then uses this argument via `${usage_file?}`.\\n\\n```toml\\n[tasks.test]\\nusage = '''\\narg \\\"<file>\\\" help=\\\"The file to test\\\" default=\\\"src/main.rs\\\"\\n'''\\nrun = 'cargo test ${usage_file?}'\\n```\\n\\n--------------------------------\\n\\n### Define Task Arguments with Usage Field (Mise TOML)\\n\\nSource: https://github.com/jdx/mise/blob/main/docs/tasks/task-arguments.md\\n\\nDemonstrates the preferred method of defining task arguments using the 'usage' field in a mise.toml file. This approach supports various argument types like positional arguments, flags with defaults and environment variable backing, and choices. Arguments are accessible as environment variables (e.g., $usage_environment) and within Tera templates (e.g., {{ usage.environment }}).\\n\\n```mise-toml\\n[tasks.deploy]\\ndescription = \\\"Deploy application\\\"\\nusage = '''\\narg \\\"<environment>\\\" help=\\\"Target environment\\\" {\\n  choices \\\"dev\\\" \\\"staging\\\" \\\"prod\\\"\\n}\\nflag \\\"-v --verbose\\\" help=\\\"Enable verbose output\\\"\\nflag \\\"--region <region>\\\" help=\\\"AWS region\\\" default=\\\"us-east-1\\\" env=\\\"AWS_REGION\\\"\\n'''\\n\\nrun = '''\\necho \\\"Deploying to ${usage_environment?} in ${usage_region?}\\\"\\n[[ \\\"${usage_verbose?}\\\" == \\\"true\\\" ]] && set -x\\n./deploy.sh \\\"${usage_environment?}\\\" \\\"${usage_region?}\\\"\\n'''\\n\\n```\\n\\n```mise-toml\\n[tasks.deploy]\\ndescription = \\\"Deploy application\\\"\\nusage = '''\\narg \\\"<environment>\\\" help=\\\"Target environment\\\"\\nflag \\\"-v --verbose\\\" help=\\\"Enable verbose output\\\"\\nflag \\\"--region <region>\\\" help=\\\"AWS region\\\" default=\\\"us-east-1\\\"\\n'''\\nrun = '''\\necho \\\"Deploying to {{ usage.environment }} in {{ usage.region }}\\\"\\n{% if usage.verbose %}\\n  echo \\\"Verbose mode enabled\\\"\\n{% endif %}\\n'''\\n\\n```\"}]}]},\"uuid\":\"d7622b11-e895-447d-825e-d16740edfe65\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-27T05:12:26.808Z\",\"toolUseResult\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"### Define File Task Arguments with #MISE/#USAGE Comments\\n\\nSource: https://github.com/jdx/mise/blob/main/docs/tasks/task-arguments.md\\n\\nThis snippet demonstrates how to define arguments for a file task using #MISE and #USAGE comments directly within a bash script. It shows how to declare arguments, flags with help text and default values, and how to access these variables within the script. This method allows for self-contained task definitions.\\n\\n```bash\\n#!/usr/bin/env bash\\n#MISE description \\\"Deploy application\\\"\\n#USAGE arg \\\"<environment>\\\" help=\\\"Deployment environment\\\" {\\n#USAGE   choices \\\"dev\\\" \\\"staging\\\" \\\"prod\\\"\\n#USAGE }\\n#USAGE flag \\\"--dry-run\\\" help=\\\"Preview changes without deploying\\\"\\n#USAGE flag \\\"--region <region>\\\" help=\\\"AWS region\\\" default=\\\"us-east-1\\\" env=\\\"AWS_REGION\\\"\\n\\nENVIRONMENT=\\\"${usage_environment?}\\\"\\nREGION=\\\"${usage_region?}\\\"\\nDRY_RUN=\\\"${usage_dry_run:-false}\\\"\\n\\nif [[ \\\"$DRY_RUN\\\" == \\\"true\\\" ]]; then\\n  echo \\\"DRY RUN: Would deploy to $ENVIRONMENT in $REGION\\\"\\nelse\\n  echo \\\"Deploying to $ENVIRONMENT in $REGION...\\\"\\n  ./scripts/deploy.sh \\\"$ENVIRONMENT\\\" \\\"$REGION\\\"\\nfi\\n\\n```\\n\\n--------------------------------\\n\\n### File Task with Usage Arguments (Bash)\\n\\nSource: https://github.com/jdx/mise/blob/main/docs/tasks/task-configuration.md\\n\\nThis bash script demonstrates how to define task arguments and flags directly within comments using the `#USAGE` directive. It supports `env` attributes for enviro